Everything is matching, and the PU scope and mount are authentic. Rifle includes the bayonet and cleaning kit. The rifle was arsenal-refurbished after WWII and is in excellent shape - one of the nicer looking stocks I've seen on a Mosin, with one very shallow gouge in the wood near the trigger guard. The rifle fell out of its rack and the interior lens was either cracked or knocked loose - the outer lenses are still in perfect shape and the scope tube itself is undamaged. I simply wasn't getting enough use out of this rifle to justify spending time and money trying to get it repaired or replaced.
